/*
 * ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 *  Smart OS — XIAO ESP32-S3 Sense firmware (v3.32 final)
 *  Hardware: Seeed XIAO ESP32-S3 Sense + 0.91" SSD1306 OLED
 *
 *  ⚠ DO NOT lower config.frame_size in initCamera() below FRAMESIZE_UXGA.
 *    The esp32-camera driver allocates DMA buffers at init and does NOT
 *    resize them when set_framesize() is called later. AI/Timelapse modes
 *    request UXGA at runtime — initializing at VGA causes a DMA buffer
 *    overflow on the first non-Guard photo capture, resetting the chip.
 *    We init at UXGA, then drop the sensor to VGA for default operation.
 *
 *  Six modes navigated via PDM-microphone tap detection (no buttons):
 *    Guard / AI Assist / Classic / Voice / Timelapse / IT Support / Settings
 *
 *  Tap conventions:
 *    1× tap → scroll / single action     2× tap → confirm / enter mode
 *    3× tap → exit / unlock              auto-lock after 40 s idle
 *
 *  Companion VPS backend: vps_backend/main.py (FastAPI + Gemini + Telegram).
 *
 *  Configuration (WiFi, VPS host, ports) is in wifi_config.h.
 *  See wifi_config.example.h for the template.
 *
 *  Flashing: USB-OTG bootloader, hold BOOT, tap RESET, release BOOT,
 *  then upload from Arduino IDE. (No OTA in this build — TinyUSB and
 *  ArduinoOTA conflicted on the S3.)
 * ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
 */

